\sum_{i=1}^{p-1} r_i h_i \left( \frac{a}{a+b} X_p \right) \nonumber \\
& = & \textrm E (\mu_p \mid X_p) - \frac{\sigma^2 (\eta^2 - \gamma^2)}{1 + \sigma^2} \sum_{i=1}^{p-1} h_i \left( \frac{\gamma^2 + \sigma^2\eta^2}{1+\sigma^2} X_p \right).
\end{eqnarray*}
The proof is complete.
\end{proof}

Proposition \ref{prop:2} confirms the existence of the selection bias in general. Furthermore, it provides the following interesting insights:
