\item \label{intuition:2}
For fixed $\gamma$, $\eta$, $p$ and $X_p,$ the selection bias goes to zero as $\sigma$ goes to zero. This is intuitive because $X_p$ approaches $\mu_p$ as $\sigma$ goes to zero, and therefore the fact that $X_p = \max_{1 \le i \le p}X_i$ becomes irrelevant;

